# {{ project_name }}

This is an `keel` repository: git-native project management with a
concept graph, designed to be driven primarily by Claude Code (or similar
agents) loaded with the `project-manager` skill.

## For the PM agent

If you are an agent loaded with the `project-manager` skill, your entry
point is `.claude/skills/project-manager/SKILL.md`. Before doing any work,
run:

```
keel brief
```

This prints the project config, active enums, templates, and next-available
IDs — everything you need to start creating or updating entities. Then
read the relevant workflow reference from the skill (usually
`WORKFLOWS_INITIAL_SCOPING.md` or `WORKFLOWS_INCREMENTAL_UPDATE.md`).

After every batch of file writes, run:

```
keel validate --strict
```

This is the gate. Parse the JSON, fix every error, re-run until exit 0.

## For humans

- `issues/` — one YAML file per issue
- `nodes/` — one YAML file per concept node
- `sessions/` — agent session definitions and runtime state
- `issues/<KEY>/` — per-issue developer notes, comments, verified records
- `project.yaml` — project config (status flow, repos, orchestration defaults)
- `.claude/skills/project-manager/` — PM skill (loaded by agents; edit to
  customise agent behaviour for this project)

Humans typically interact with this repo through the agent rather than by
editing YAML directly. If you need to make changes, ask the agent.

